Your Week in Review note on Rudolf Hess's death (Aug. 23) states that Hitler was elected <RP Category='HEAD_OF_STATE_TAG'><HR>Chancellor</HR> of Germany</RP>. 

Hitler was appointed <RP Category='HEAD_OF_STATE_TAG'><HR>Chancellor</HR></RP>, not elected. 

German industrialists backing Hitler became concerned about the declining Nazi vote and persuaded <RP Category='HEAD_OF_STATE_TAG'><HR>President</HR> Paul von Hindenburg</RP> to appoint Hitler as <RP Category='HEAD_OF_STATE_TAG'><HR>Reich Chancellor</HR></RP>, which occurred on Jan. 30, 1933.




